  "prompt": "What are the good game stalls ideas that which gives much money than others at college fests?",
  "response": "Creating a successful game stall at college fests can involve a combination of engaging activities, appealing prizes, and effective marketing. Here are some ideas that could generate good revenue:\n\n1. **Ring Toss**: A classic game where participants toss rings over bottles. Simple to set up and offers a good profit margin.\n\n2. **Balloon Pop**: Sell darts or sticks and have participants pop balloons for prizes. The thrill of popping a balloon can attract many players.\n\n3. **Mini Golf**: Set up a mini-golf course with a few holes. Charge a fee per round, and you can also offer prizes for best scores.\n\n4. **Mystery Box Challenge**: Participants pay to pick a mystery box; some have valuable prizes, while others may contain small trinkets. \n\n5. **Spin the Wheel**: Create a spinning prize wheel with different prizes. Charge a fee per spin, and include high-value prizes to create excitement.\n\n6. **Photo Booth with Props**: Set up a themed photo booth where students can take fun pictures. Charge for prints or digital copies.\n\n7. **Karaoke Competition**: Host a karaoke competition with an entry fee and prizes for the best performances. It can draw in crowds and involve goodwill.\n\n8. **Escape Room Game**: Create a mini escape room challenge that can be completed in a short time. Charge groups to participate.\n\n9. **Whack-a-Mole**: Create a simplified version of this classic arcade game using plush toys and mallets. Offer prizes for high scores.\n\n10. **Digital Gaming Station**: Set up gaming consoles with popular video games and charge for time slots or organize tournaments.\n\n11. **Bingo for Prizes**: Run a bingo game with interesting prizes. Simple to organize and can attract many participants.\n\n12. **Target Shooting**: Use Nerf guns or soft darts to hit targets for prizes. This can be fun and engaging for all ages.\n\n13. **Trivia Contest**: Host trivia rounds on popular topics. Charge an entry fee and offer prizes for correct answers.\n\n14. **Board Game Caf\u00e9**: Set up an area for people to play popular board games and charge a small fee for the time they play.\n\n15. **Tug of War**: Combine physical activity with friendly competition. Charge teams to enter, and offer a trophy or prize.\n\nWhen promoting your stall, be sure to use attractive signage, social media, and word of mouth to draw in crowds. Offering bundled pricing, such as discounts for multiple attempts or team entries, can also encourage more participation.",
